The [source code][1] of the OpenJDK version of `GSSUtil` is available online. Looking at the code (and the comments) you can see it relies on package private APIs of the Sun&#39;s implementations of GSSName and GSSCredential, specifically: `GSSNameImpl`, `GSSNameSpi`, `Krb5NameElement` and `GSSCredentialImpl`.&lt;br&gt;
The IBM Java SDK `ibmjgssprovider.jar` contains similar IBM implementations which can be used to achieve the same functionality. Take a look at the `com.ibm.security.jgss` and `com.ibm.security.krb5` packages.


  [1]: http://grepcode.com/file/repository.grepcode.com/java/root/jdk/openjdk/6-b14/sun/security/jgss/GSSUtil.java

